Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper discusses language processing tools and techniques for handling lexical and syntactic ambiguities, which falls under the scope of natural language processing and computational linguistics.
2. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper presents Lamb and Fence algorithms for language processing, which can be applied to programming languages as well.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper mentions model-based language processing tools, which may involve machine learning techniques for language modeling and disambiguation.
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses language design and processing tools, which are relevant to software engineering for developing programming languages and compilers.
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper's focus on handling ambiguities and constraints in language processing may involve AI techniques such as rule-based systems and constraint satisfaction.
